lead_paragraph: Allisen Corpuz, 10, of Kapolei, Hawaii, shot a 15-over-par 88 in the second round of the United States Women’s Amateur Public Links Championship in Erin, Wis. Her two-day total of 169 was nine strokes over the 160 cut for the 64 golfers advancing to match play, but it was pretty good for a fifth-grader who is 5 feet and weighs 111 pounds.
